# Touchpoint 1, mechanically enforced: the spec, the invariants, and the ADW's
# own encoded config are the owner's domain. Any PR touching these requires
# @bugabinga's review — no agent merges a change here, so agents genuinely cannot
# rewrite their own rules. Kept deliberately wide: CLAUDE.md (the rules every
# agent inherits), all of .claude/ (agents, skills, settings), and all of .github/
# (workflows, labels, rulesets, Dependabot, templates) are protected, not just the
# agent files — the earlier gap let a PR quietly edit CLAUDE.md, a skill, or the
# label set and auto-merge it.
docs/SPEC.md                         @bugabinga
docs/PROJECT-INVARIANTS.md           @bugabinga
docs/plans/AGENTIC-DEVELOPMENT.md    @bugabinga
CLAUDE.md                            @bugabinga
**/CLAUDE.md                         @bugabinga
.claude/                             @bugabinga
.github/                             @bugabinga
